subsection.p:
A business venture calculates its profitprofit by subtracting its costscost from its revenuerevenue, the amount of money it takes in from sales.
    \blert{\text{Profit} = \text{Revenue} -\text{Cost}}
Cost is usually calculated as the sum of fixed costs, or overhead, and variable costs, the cost of labor and materials to produce its product. Revenue is the product of the selling price per item times the number of items sold. If the company’s revenue exactly equals its costs (so that their profit is zero), we say that the business venture will break evenbreak even. ~\alert{\text{[TK]}}
